'''Group D of the [[2003 FIFA Women's World Cup]]''' was one of four groups of nations, consisting of [[Australia women's national soccer team|Australia]], [[China women's national football team|China]], [[Ghana women's national football team|Ghana]] and [[Russia women's national football team|Russia]]. It began on 21 September and ended on 28 September. Most matches were played at [[The Home Depot Center]] in [[Carson, California|Carson]], save the last two that were played at [[PGE Park]] in [[Portland, Oregon|Portland]]. China PR topped the group despite their lackluster performances, followed to the next round by Russia. Australia and Ghana didn't make the second round.

