{{Ho Chi Minh Thought sidebar}}
{{Contains Vietnamese text}}
'''Ho Chi Minh Thought''', or '''Ho Chi Minh Ideology''', ({{lang-vi|Tư tưởng Hồ Chí Minh}}) is a [[political philosophy]] that builds upon [[Marxism–Leninism]] and the ideology of [[Ho Chi Minh]]. It was first formalised by the [[Communist Party of Vietnam]] in 1991. Ho Chi Minh Thought is a broad term for political theories and policies that are seen by their proponents as representing Marxism–Leninism adapted to Vietnamese circumstances and specific time periods. The ideology includes views on the basic issues of the Vietnamese Revolution, specifically the application and development of Marxism-Leninism to the material conditions of Vietnam. The contents of Ho Chi Minh Thought was codified and developed by the [[Communist Party of Vietnam]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www6.cityu.edu.hk/searc/Data/FileUpload/325/WP121_12_Vu.pdf|title=The persistence of Single-Party Dictatorships: The Case of Vietnam|number=121|date=January 2012|first=Vu|last=Tuong|publisher=Southeast Asia Research Centre, City University of Hong Kong|series=SEARC Working Paper Series|page=14}}{{Dead link|date=January 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=The Organization of the Practice of the Ho Chi Minh Movement and the Learning of its Moral Codes|url=http://www.haugiang.gov.vn/Portal/DATA/sites/10/chuyende/HOCTAPGUONGDAODUCHOCHIMINH/|publisher=[[Vietnam Communist Party]]|accessdate=24 March 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110320012632/http://www.haugiang.gov.vn/Portal/DATA/sites/10/chuyende/HOCTAPGUONGDAODUCHOCHIMINH/|archive-date=20 March 2011|url-status=dead}}</ref>
The Communist Party of Vietnam defines Marxism-Leninism and Ho Chi Minh Thought as a guideline for all actions and victories of the Vietnamese revolution.<ref>Đảng Cộng sản Việt Nam xác định lấy ''[[Chủ nghĩa Mác-Lênin]] và tư tưởng Hồ Chí Minh là kim chỉ nam cho mọi hành động và thắng lợi của cách mạng Việt Nam''.</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.cpv.org.vn/cpv/Modules/News/NewsDetail.aspx?co_id=30106&cn_id=443473 |title=Điều lệ Đảng Cộng sản Việt Nam, thông qua ngày 19 tháng 01 năm 2011 |access-date=4 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130125053016/http://www.cpv.org.vn/cpv/Modules/News/NewsDetail.aspx?co_id=30106&cn_id=443473 |archive-date=25 January 2013 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>[http://www.vinhphuc.gov.vn/ct/cms/hochiminh/Lists/NghienCuuTraoDoi/View_Detail.aspx?ItemID=8 Chủ nghĩa Mác – Lênin và tư tưởng Hồ Chí Minh là kim chỉ nam cho mọi hành động và thắng lợi của cách mạng Việt Nam, Trần Viết Dương, Trường Chính trị tỉnh Vĩnh Phúc]</ref> Ho Chi Minh Thought, while named after the Vietnamese revolutionary and President, does not necessarily reflect the ideology of [[Ho Chi Minh]], rather Ho Chi Minh Thought refers to the official ideology of the Communist Party of Vietnam.<ref>{{cite book |doi=10.4135/9781452234168.n150 |chapter=Ho Chi Minh Thought |title=Encyclopedia of Modern Political Thought |year=2013 |isbn=9780872899100 }}</ref><ref>{{cite book | last = Gillespie | first = John Stanley | title = Transplanting Commercial Law Reform: Developing a 'Rule of Law' in Vietnam  | ref = harv | publisher = Ashgate Publishing | year = 2006 | isbn = 9780754647041 }}</ref><ref name=thayer>{{cite journal |last1=Thayer |first1=Carlyle A. |title=Political Legitimacy in Vietnam: Challenge and Response |journal=Politics & Policy |date=8 June 2010 |volume=38 |issue=3 |pages=423–444 |doi=10.1111/j.1747-1346.2010.00242.x }}</ref>

== Origins ==
Ho Chi Minh Thought was influenced by [[Vietnamese culture]], the [[French revolution]], and [[Marxism–Leninism]]. Similar to [[Maoism]], at the core of Ho Chi Minh Thought is that the peasantry is the [[Vanguardism|revolutionary vanguard]] in pre-industrial societies, rather than the [[proletariat]].<ref>Hồ Chí Minh Toàn tập, tập 3, Nhà xuất bản Chính trị Quốc gia, trang 3.</ref>

Ho Chi Minh Thought is rooted in:<ref name=Curriculum />

*[[Marxism-Leninism]]{{citation needed|date=February 2020}}
*Traditional Vietnamese ideology and culture{{citation needed|date=February 2020}}
*Eastern cultural thought: [[Confucianism]], [[Buddhism]]<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Son |first1=BUI Ngoc |title=The Confucian Foundations of Hổ Chí Minh's Vision of Government / 胡志明政治思想中的儒學基礎 |journal=Journal of Oriental Studies |date=2013 |volume=46 |issue=1 |pages=35–59 |jstor=43498666 }}</ref>
*Western ideologies, specifically French and American political philosophy{{citation needed|date=January 2020}}
*Ho Chi Minh 's personal morality

=== Influence of Confucianism ===
Ho Chi Minh, the son of a Confucian scholar, studied [[Confucianism]] throughout his life and was a strong critic of Confucian ethics and ideals.<ref name=\Confucian\">{{cite journal |last1=Son |first1=Bui Ngoc |title=The Confucian Foundations of Hổ Chí Minh's Vision of Government / 胡志明政治思想中的儒學基礎 |journal=Journal of Oriental Studies |date=2013 |volume=46 |issue=1 |pages=35–59 |jstor=43498666 }}</ref> Despite this public criticism

